error: Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found: /usr/share/doc/coin-or-Dip/dip_addlibs.txt
File installed during build but not accounted for with %doc.

Created attachment 1135774 Patch to fix the FTBFS
The origin of this FTBFS is the package mixing installation of docs vis direct installation (make install, cp ...) with installation by %doc <relative file name>.
With recent versions of rpm one needs settle on one of these alternative and can't mix them anymore.
I am going to apply the patch from the attachment, which switches this package to using direct installation into %_pkgdocdir.

Packaging-wise the package now builds fine, unfortunately, now the testsuite fails on i386/rawhide:
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=13328581
As this is beyond my scope, returning bug ownership to package owner.
